13/12/2002
BUCHAREST, Romania -- Albania and Romania share views on regional integration and integration within NATO and EU structures, according to a joint statement by Albanian Foreign Minister Ilir Meta and Romanian President Ion Iliescu. 
They met Thursday (12 December) as Meta was returning from a visit to Russia. 
The officials agreed to intensify political dialogue and bilateral relations and discussed Romania's strategy and progress towards NATO and EU accession. 
That same day, the Albanian cabinet chose regional co-operation as its policy priority during a meeting of the parliamentary commission on industry. 
(ATA, Albanian Radio - 12/12/02)
